now if i want to run on different website then what changes do i have to do 

To run on a different website, you mainly need to update config + test data, and sometimes locators.

What to change
Update config/config.ini:
base_url = <new website URL>
api_base_url = <new API URL> (if API tests)
Update test data Excel:
test_data/test_cases.xlsx (or your backup file) with new pages, test values, expected results.
If element structure differs on new site, update locators/selectors in page objects/tests:
Python: files under python_framework (tests/pages/utils depending on implementation)
Java: files under java_framework/src/... (page classes/tests)
Fast way (without editing config every time)
You can pass URL at runtime:

Python URL smoke:
cd python_framework
python -m pytest tests/test_url_smoke.py -v --test-url=https://newsite.com
Python API:
python -m pytest tests/test_api.py -v --api-url=https://api.newsite.com
Java:
cd java_framework
mvn test -DtestUrl=https://newsite.com -DapiBaseUrl=https://api.newsite.com
Step-by-step for switching website
Put new site URL in config/config.ini (base_url).
Put new API URL in config/config.ini (api_base_url) if needed.
Update Excel test cases for new site flow/data.
Run smoke tests first (Python + Java).
If failures are locator-related, update selectors in framework code.
Re-run full test suite.
